В меню игры вас приветствует надпись - Поддержите Overkill!". Вы купили PayDay за 349 рублей

As one of the most classic first person shooter (FPS) games there is in the market today, you get a whole bundle of actions, the fast-paced thrill from the heists where you eventually climb up from the bottom of the pit of noobiness to the world outside the pit where the whole new heist expeirence unfold, the enjoyment when you take down special enemies in a row and then get busted by the last one behind you, the ultimate satisfaction when you and the rest of your crew work seamlessly like a charm and make your plans work.... all packed in one bloody single game called Payday the Heist.

Nothing else feels quite like the title when it comes to team collaboration and the fast-paced thrill -- anything could happen and surprise you in the last minute, and these are exactly what make this game deserve playing.

There's always a price to pay in terms of getting used to the gameplay, but once you earned your own payday because of the hardwork, nothing pays off more than the sense of achievement, with or without the achivements themselves.

This is the game that test your patience in terms of skills, the game that requires you to be dedicated enough to enjoy more and more, the game that needs you to collaborate with the rest of your team constantly, and the game that can be enjoyed both with others and just playing solo, although the difficulty of  the two may vary from one person to another.

Is there anything more enjoyable than hearing when the police are shouting to one another that they're retreating becuase of you? >;3

Pros:
- team communication system (shouting system) works like a gem, the interactive key (default by F) multitasks so well;
- the collaboration system is well designed, the visual icons  and radio heads-up in-game provided for helping players assisting one another works very well;
- every map is very unique in their own ways, providing different challenges based on the game difficulty;
- the background music is also pretty good (i enjoyed it at least), and they suit the scenario that you're in;
- each heist story is well made, pretty realistic
-a very focused shooting game that also involves strategy and planning.

Cons:
- the game sometimes could be a bit buggy, and this could be deadly when the special units are able to shoot you through the wall;
- a bit glitchy here and there, and this might ruin your plan for a heist occassionally;
- the alarm system feels less realistic than in payday 2 where people are more capable of suspecting you, while here in PDTH even if you're standing face to face in front of a guard, as long as you don't press the key to start the heist, no one will detect you;
- skill tree upgrading system could be confusing to some (there's a Tab key you use in game to pull out an overlay, and using the 1-4 number key to select which tree you want to upgrade when you level up next), and there is no way to manually respec, unless you clear the stats history.

If you like heist titles and enjoy shooters, i highly recommend you to at least  try out this game, it might not be the easiest shooters you've played, but the rewarding in the end is just as much as the potential difficulty. I got the most sense of satisfaciton from the teamplay in this game, and even if when i'm playing solo, the challenge is there, and it's even more fun to just go try them out and test yourself.

A classic that you shouldn't miss.
